# Shell Command Safety

## Safe to run without asking (auto-approve)

These commands are safe to execute freely:

- `pnpm type-check`, `pnpm lint`, `pnpm format:check`, `pnpm format`
- `pnpm test`, `pnpm build`, `pnpm clean`
- `pnpm install`
- `turbo run <task>`
- `npx tsc --noEmit`, `npx vitest`, `npx prisma generate`
- `git status`, `git diff`, `git log`, `git branch`, `git show`
- `git add`, `git commit`, `git stash`, `git checkout`
- `ls`, `cat`, `head`, `tail`, `find`, `rg`, `grep`, `wc`, `echo`

## Ask before running

These require confirmation from the developer:

- `git push` (any non-force push)
- `git rebase`
- `pnpm add` / `pnpm remove` (dependency changes)
- `pnpm dev` (long-running server)
- `prisma migrate dev` / `prisma db seed` (local DB mutations)
- `prisma db push` (can silently drop columns/data)
- `prisma db execute` (arbitrary SQL)
- `curl`, `wget` (network requests)

## Never run

These are destructive and must never be executed:

- `git push --force` or `git push --force-with-lease`
- `git reset --hard`
- `rm -rf`

